FOR THE BLIND PEOPLE SEE: illustration in ink pen and black ink. Face with fleshy heart-shaped mouth with paint on the upper lip, small round nose, medium spaced eyes, eyebrows half filled with long hairs and with 5 small dots painted symmetrically on the forehead. Without showing the hair, covered by a dark scarf.

MY STORY:
I chose this name because I like to dress in different genders according to my mood and I can use it at all times. Most of the time I wear a hood or a headscarf. I started training so that people wouldn't notice me on the street but they say that my face is too striking. Now I study people's bodily behavior and I can flow through any of them with ease.
